{"id":297,"date":"2025-06-04T10:20:19","date_gmt":"2025-06-04T15:20:19","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/garageup.com\/?p=297"},"modified":"2025-06-18T10:37:28","modified_gmt":"2025-06-18T15:37:28","slug":"garage-floor-contractor","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/garageup.com\/blog\/2025\/06\/04\/garage-floor-contractor\/","title":{"rendered":"Your Garage Floor Deserves More Than Concrete"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Most people don\u2019t think about this: you walk on your garage floor more than your living room rug. Yet, for decades, it\u2019s been overlooked\u2014just dull concrete stained with oil and age. But that\u2019s changing fast. Epoxy flooring is exploding in popularity, and with good reason. According to home improvement experts, garage upgrades are one of the top ROI improvements homeowners can make, and epoxy floors sit at the top of the list.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>At Garage Up Austin, we believe your garage should be just as functional and attractive as the rest of your home. Whether you\u2019re parking your car, storing gear, or using it as a workshop, a sleek, tough epoxy floor adds comfort, style, and serious performance. Let\u2019s walk through what makes epoxy flooring such a game-changer\u2014and how it pairs perfectly with our garage door expertise.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"819\" src=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-7-1024x819.png\" alt=\"a garage floor with new epoxy flooring installed by garage up austin\" class=\"wp-image-322\" srcset=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-7-1024x819.png 1024w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-7-300x240.png 300w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-7-768x614.png 768w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-7-1536x1229.png 1536w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-7.png 1875w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>What Is Epoxy Garage Flooring?<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p> <a href=\"https:\/\/purepoxy.com\/systems\/purepoxy-flakes\/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https:\/\/purepoxy.com\/systems\/purepoxy-flakes\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Epoxy garage flooring<\/a> is a strong, resin-based coating made by mixing epoxy resin with a hardener. Once applied over concrete, it creates a smooth, high-gloss surface that\u2019s both durable and beautiful. This isn\u2019t just a quick fix or a layer of paint\u2014it\u2019s a chemical bond that fuses with your floor.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You\u2019ve probably seen epoxy floors in car dealerships or showrooms. That shine? That clean, polished look? Yep, that\u2019s epoxy. But it\u2019s not just for businesses anymore. Homeowners across Austin are bringing it into their garage floor\u2014and loving the results.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Where Epoxy Garage Floors Are Used:<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Garages and workshops<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Home gyms<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Basements<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Commercial spaces<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Warehouses and industrial facilities<br><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>The Big Benefits of Epoxy Garage Flooring<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Choosing the right floor isn&#8217;t just about looks. Epoxy delivers real, measurable value\u2014especially in a high-use area like your garage. Here&#8217;s why it stands out.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Long-Lasting Durability<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Epoxy is shock-resistant, scratch-proof, and tough as nails. Drop tools? No problem. Park heavy vehicles? Bring it on. It holds up for years without cracks or crumbling.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Easy to Clean<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the best parts? No more scrubbing oil stains or sweeping endless dust. Epoxy repels dirt, grime, and spills. A quick mop or hose-down is all it takes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Water &amp; Chemical Resistance<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Got leaks or chemical spills? Epoxy doesn\u2019t care. Its sealed surface blocks out water, gasoline, and even harsh cleaning agents\u2014making it ideal for garage environments.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Safe &amp; Slip-Resistant<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>With the right finish, epoxy floors provide traction even when wet. That means fewer slips and better footing, especially important in busy garages.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Stylish and Customizable<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This isn&#8217;t just gray anymore. Epoxy floors come in bold colors, metallic finishes, and even custom flake designs to match your car, your home, or your mood.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"819\" src=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-9-1024x819.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-323\" srcset=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-9-1024x819.png 1024w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-9-300x240.png 300w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-9-768x614.png 768w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/06\/GU-website-photos-9.png 1500w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Popular Types of Epoxy Garage Floors<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Different spaces call for different styles. Let\u2019s break down the most popular options we install for homeowners in Austin.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Self-Leveling Epoxy<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Perfect for uneven surfaces, this type spreads out smoothly and fills imperfections in your concrete. It&#8217;s sleek and professional.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Epoxy Flake Floors<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Tiny chips of vinyl or stone are added to the epoxy for texture, color, and grip. Great for hiding dirt and adding a pop of style.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Metallic Epoxy<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Want something bold? This option creates a shimmery, 3D look that\u2019s pure eye candy. Ideal for man caves and showcase garages.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Epoxy Mortar Systems<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>For heavy-duty use, like home workshops or commercial garages, epoxy mortar is as tough as it gets.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step-by-Step: How Epoxy Garage Floors Are Installed<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Let\u2019s break down how the process works, so you know what to expect if you choose Garage Up Austin to handle your garage floor transformation.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 1: Floor Prep<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We start by cleaning and grinding the surface. This removes stains, opens the pores of the concrete, and helps the epoxy bond like glue.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 2: Repair Cracks<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Any cracks or chips in your concrete are patched with industrial-strength filler.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 3: Primer Coat<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A primer layer goes down to seal the floor and lock in the epoxy\u2019s strength.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 4: Epoxy Application<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We roll on the epoxy, add flakes (if desired), and spread it evenly across the surface.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 5: Topcoat &amp; Cure<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A protective topcoat is added, and then the floor cures over 24\u201372 hours depending on the system. After that, it\u2019s ready to handle anything!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"819\" src=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/GU-website-photos-10-1024x819.png\" alt=\"a garage up technician applying a sealant coating to the new epoxy flooring\" class=\"wp-image-56\" srcset=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/GU-website-photos-10-1024x819.png 1024w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/GU-website-photos-10-300x240.png 300w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/GU-website-photos-10-768x614.png 768w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/GU-website-photos-10.png 1500w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Best Places to Use Epoxy in Your Garage<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>At Garage Up Austin, we don\u2019t just think about garage doors\u2014we think about how the whole space functions. Epoxy works wonders in:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Parking Areas<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Tired of concrete that flakes and stains? Epoxy resists oil, heat, and tire marks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Storage Zones<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Turn cluttered storage corners into clean, wipeable surfaces.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Home Gyms or Hobby Spaces<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Whether you lift weights or build furniture, a strong floor makes the space more usable.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Garage Entryways<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Create a polished transition from garage to home with a design that flows with your interior.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>What\u2019s the Cost of Epoxy Garage Flooring in 2025?<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Good news: epoxy is one of the most cost-effective flooring solutions you can buy\u2014especially over the long haul. Most residential epoxy floors in Austin cost between $4 to $10 per square foot, depending on:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Floor condition (damaged concrete may require extra prep)<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Floor size<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Type of epoxy system used<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Custom colors or flakes<br><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Compared to tile, concrete polishing, or vinyl\u2014epoxy offers <strong>more value per dollar<\/strong>, thanks to its lifespan and low maintenance.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Design Ideas That Set Your Garage Apart<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Your garage doesn\u2019t have to look like a mechanic\u2019s shop (unless you want it to!). Epoxy opens up tons of design possibilities.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Bold Color Combos<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Pick a high-contrast flake mix to complement your car or garage walls.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Sleek Metallics<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Bring showroom vibes to your home with swirling silver, bronze, or copper tones.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Branded Floors<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Want your college team logo or a family monogram? Custom designs are totally possible.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Neutral and Clean<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If minimal is your style, go with gray tones and subtle texture for a crisp, modern look.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Maintenance Tips: Keep Your Floor Looking Fresh<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>An epoxy floor doesn\u2019t demand much, but a little TLC keeps it looking sharp.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Sweep or mop regularly<\/strong> to remove dust and grit.<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Use soft cleaners<\/strong>\u2014avoid citrus or vinegar-based products.<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Add mats<\/strong> under tires or heavy equipment for extra protection.<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Reapply topcoat<\/strong> every 5\u20137 years if needed.<br><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>At Garage Up Austin, we offer touch-up services and protective sealing to extend the life of your floor.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"819\" src=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/GU-website-photos-38-1024x819.png\" alt=\"A newly renovated garage that includes new storage units, slat walls, and hex lights installed by professional technicians at Garage Up\" class=\"wp-image-133\" srcset=\"https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/GU-website-photos-38-1024x819.png 1024w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/GU-website-photos-38-300x240.png 300w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/GU-website-photos-38-768x614.png 768w, https:\/\/garageup.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/GU-website-photos-38.png 1500w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>How Epoxy Compares to Other Garage Flooring Options<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Let\u2019s quickly compare epoxy to what you might be considering:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><tbody><tr><td><strong>Flooring Type<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Durability<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Maintenance<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Style Options<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Cost (avg.)<\/strong><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Epoxy<\/strong><\/td><td>\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605<\/td><td>\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605<\/td><td>\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2606<\/td><td>$4\u2013$10\/sqft<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Polished Concrete<\/td><td>\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2606<\/td><td>\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2606<\/td><td>\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2606\u26